<br>
My votes would go to Crouching Tiger Hidden Dragon, the second star wars (newer one) where yoda fights, im sorry but he kicked some SERIOUS ass in that, pirates of the carribean wasnt bad fight wise...<br>
<br>
Movie swordfights = long, flashy, showy, clashing swords and backflips.<br>
<br>
Actual swordfights = quick and to the point (no pun intended)<br>
<br>
