<br>
Samurai duels were usually over in the first sequence.<br>
<br>
However, it wasn't uncommon for Victorian duels to last for days according to history.  Which is insane.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Anyone who has actually trained can watch a movie and pick the fightscenes apart<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yeah, Jackie Chan's blocks are so fake.  A wave block is never going to work against a thousand pounds of pressure, which isn't an uncommon blow for a trained fighter.<br>
<br>
I thought the second Prequel fight scenes for StarWars sucked.  When Anakin gets his forearm severed, it's like he just stands there and lets it happen.  What the hell?<br>
<br>
I enjoyed the duel at the end of Rob Roy.  Rob won it Scotts' style, too.  But if you've seen this fight, you were probably like me and thinking &quot;Okay, why the hell is this guy trying to defend against a rapier with one of the heaviest weapons ever, when he could snap the bastard's blade in two with one centered swing!&quot; and dude, I don't care what weapon you're using, he still missed a lot of parries for an experienced fighter.<br>
<br>
Matrix: Reloaded.  Scorpion Kick performed by Trinity.  Sure, it's supposed to be fake, but that kick has no practicality or effect, yet requires months of stretching to even make the mark.  It doesn't even hurt, is likely to miss and leaves you extremely vulnerable, which you already are if you've bent to the side of your attacker. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=takkonsmakafu>Takkon Smakafu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 640<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/9/03 2:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2188.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best Ever Swordfight in a Movie!</span><hr size=1> Yoda vs Duku - Episode 2<br>
